  "prompt": "How much did it cost to build Walt Disney World?",
  "response": "Building Walt Disney World in Florida was a monumental project that involved significant financial investment over several years. Here's a breakdown of the costs:\n\n### **Initial Construction Costs**\n- **Estimated Cost at the Time:** The initial construction of Walt Disney World, which officially opened on October 1, 1971, cost approximately **$400 million USD**. This investment covered land acquisition, infrastructure development, theme parks (including the Magic Kingdom), hotels, transportation systems (like the monorail), and other essential facilities.\n\n### **Inflation-Adjusted Costs**\n- **Adjusted for Inflation:** Accounting for inflation, the initial $400 million in 1971 would be roughly equivalent to **over $2.5 billion USD** in today's dollars (as of 2023). This adjustment provides a sense of the massive scale and investment required at the time.\n\n### **Total Investment Over the Years**\n- **Ongoing Investments:** Since its opening, Walt Disney World has undergone continuous expansion and enhancement. Over the decades, Disney has invested **more than $20 billion USD** into the resort. This includes the development of additional theme parks like EPCOT, Disney's Hollywood Studios, and Disney's Animal Kingdom, as well as numerous resorts, water parks, entertainment venues, and infrastructure improvements.\n\n### **Key Points to Consider**\n- **Land Acquisition:** Disney purchased approximately 27,443 acres of land in Central Florida, a considerable portion of which remains as part of the resort's extensive property.\n- **Innovative Infrastructure:** Walt Disney World was pioneering in its use of private transportation systems, large-scale landscaping, and theming, all of which contributed to its high initial and ongoing costs.\n- **Economic Impact:** The investment not only built a world-famous entertainment destination but also spurred economic growth in the region, creating thousands of jobs and attracting millions of visitors each year.\n\n### **Conclusion**\nBuilding Walt Disney World required an initial investment of around **$400 million USD** in the early 1970s, with total investments exceeding **$20 billion USD** over the subsequent decades. This massive financial commitment has resulted in one of the most successful and enduring entertainment complexes in the world.",
